The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, November 26, 2002 				 Clash of ethics
																								New Delhi, Nov. 25: Corporate governance led to corporate clash of opinions at the forum today, when India Incs flamboyant icon Rahul Bajaj met the high networthed Azim Premji of Wipro in a session on business ethics. 																								While Premji approved of engaging board members, including non executive directors, as consultants and advisors, Bajaj said non-executive directors should stick to their role as directors. If the expertise of non executive director needs to be engaged by a firm, that should be done with full emoluments. But they should quit as non-executive directors, he said. 
